node.statement: CASE 2 CONCLUSION: In all sub-cases of Case 2 (g_1(B) != B), either: (A) We reduce to Case 1 structure where a block contains sufficient core elements, leading to contradiction. (B) The orbit analysis forces block sizes to be inconsistent (blocks in same orbit must have equal size, but constraints from multiple generators force unequal sizes). (C) The interplay between g_1, g_2, g_3 orbits forces the overall orbit under H to be transitive on blocks, meaning only one block exists, so |B| = N. CONTRADICTION in all cases.
